messages.content: Hello! Thank you for joining me for this interview. Could you please start by telling me a little bit about your experience with interviews?

my experience with interviews well I've been doing for a long time I started as a systems analyst at frog and then at Deloitte I came actually Friday with Hartman and we did a lot of interviews there but at Deloitte I've been a user researcher I guess it frog too and been connecting interviews for 25 years

That's quite an impressive background in conducting interviews! With your extensive experience in user research and conducting interviews, what are some key insights you have gained over the years regarding effective interviewing techniques? How do you ensure you get valuable information from the interviewees?

Of course, thank you for having me. I have participated in several job interviews throughout my career, both as an interviewee and as an interviewer. I have experienced various interview formats, from traditional one-on-one interviews to panel interviews and even virtual interviews. Each experience has provided me with valuable insights into the interview process.
